, it’s the weekend, and that means it’s time for some good old-fashioned time-wasting.

I’ve been playing a lot of the new Call of Duty: Ghosts lately, and I’ve noticed a few things that are a little strange.

First of all, the game seems to be a lot more forgiving than previous Call of Duty games. I’m not sure if it’s because I’ve played the game more or because the game is actually easier, but I feel like I’m able to get away with a lot more mistakes than I used to.

Secondly, I feel like the game is a lot more linear than it used to be. There are still a few open areas, but for the most part, the game seems to funnel you down a specific path.

Lastly, I feel like the game is a lot more focused on killstreaks than it used to be. In the past, killstreaks were a nice bonus, but they weren’t necessarily the focus of the game. In Ghosts, however, it seems like killstreaks are the be-all, end-all.

Don’t get me wrong, I’m still enjoying the game. But it’s definitely different than what I’m used to.
